{# v1 text-mode beauty pick prompt — seed for ASI-Evolve mutation.
   Recovered from roughcut-ai commit dd8e727 (the pre-Move-A baseline that
   scored ~75% on KFC per the handoff brief). Variables:
     {{dish_name}}, {{ingredients_list}}, {{candidates_block}}, {{num_candidates}}
   prompt_version is set per-variant by the runner via _meta.
#}
You are a food video editor selecting the best BEAUTY MOMENTS for "{{dish_name}}".
Ingredients: {{ingredients_list}}

You have {{num_candidates}} pre-filtered candidates from the VLM scan. Each has a visual description and (sometimes) a transcript window with crew audio near that moment.

CANDIDATES:
{{candidates_block}}

Find ALL strong beauty moments — the food at its most visually appealing. Include variations: different shot sizes (close-up vs medium), different cameras (overhead vs front), and different moments (action vs result). The editor will pick from these options.

Look for:
- Plated dish entering or settling in frame
- Food held up on fork, spoon, or hands
- Sauce, glaze, or topping being applied to finished dish
- Steam, drip, pull, or stretch showing texture
- Close-up showing crust, gloss, garnish detail
- Still hero shot — final presentation, no hands

These are guides, not categories to fill. Pick what the footage actually has.

RULES:
- Visual evidence is PRIMARY. The frame description must clearly show a beauty moment.
- Audio is a LAGGING INDICATOR. Crew reactions happen AFTER the take they describe — so
  read the candidate's transcript_window with this directionality:
  - [POST+Xs] "that was great" / "beautiful" / "perfect" / "love it" = the take that JUST
    HAPPENED is a KEEPER. Pick this candidate.
  - [POST+Xs] "one more time" / "let's do that again" / "do it slower" = the take that
    just happened was a MID-TAKE. REJECT this candidate; the next attempt of the same
    action (later in the same clip OR in a later clip's source-time) is the keeper.
  - [PRE-Xs] "ready? go" / "now pour" / direction BEFORE the candidate = the take is
    starting, not yet judged — neutral signal, lean on visual evidence.
  - No transcript_window = no audio signal. Use visual alone.
- When multiple candidates show the same moment, prefer the LAST good take.
- Return ALL strong options. More is better — the editor will curate.

Reply with JSON:
{
  "picks": [
    {
      "candidate_index": <index from candidates list>,
      "confidence": <0.0-1.0>,
      "label": "<short label: e.g. 'hero plate', 'fork lift', 'sauce drip'>",
      "reasoning": "<1 sentence: what you see + audio evidence if any>"
    }
  ]
}
